== Life and career ==
Pell has been a writer for ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' since 1995. She also was a producer and writer for the sitcom ''[[30 Rock]]'', and is credited for writing the episodes [[Argus (30 Rock)|"Argus"]] and [[Floyd (30 Rock)|"Floyd"]]. In 2006, a pilot she wrote, ''Thick and Thin'', was picked up by NBC for 13 episodes, with Pell as executive producer.<ref name=htt/> Pell has worked with [[Judd Apatow]] providing additional writing for the films ''[[Bridesmaids (2011 film)|Bridesmaids]]'' and ''[[This is 40]]''.
As an actress, Pell appeared in several episodes of ''30 Rock'' as the wife of [[Pete Hornberger]], and played the mother of [[Ron Swanson]] in a 2011 episode of ''[[Parks and Recreation]]''.<ref name=var/> She has also appeared as an [[Extra (acting)|extra]] or in bit parts in dozens of SNL sketches. Pell voices Gadget Gal in the [[Hulu]] original series ''[[The Awesomes]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mynews13.com/content/news/cfnews13/on-the-town/article.html/content/news/articles/cfn/2014/9/23/snl_s_paula_pell_wai.html|title=SNL's Paula Pell 'waiting for the action figure'|work=[[News 13 (Central Florida)|News 13]]|last=Walker|first=Allison|date=September 23, 2014|accessdate=January 12, 2015}}</ref>
She has a small cameo in the 2013 [[comedy]] film ''[[Anchorman 2: The Legend Continues]]''. She co-created web series ''Hudson Valley Ballers'' with fellow SNL writer and long time friend [[James Anderson (writer)|James Anderson]] with whom she also co-stars.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/12/17/hudson-valley-ballers_n_4461705.html|title= 10 Reasons You Should Watch 'Hudson Valley Ballers' Right Now|last1= Hartsell|first1= Carol|last2= |first2= |date= 17 December 2013|website= [[The Huffington Post]]|publisher= |access-date= 12 July 2015|quote=}}</ref> [[Tina Fey]] produced and starred in Pell's first feature screenplay, ''[[Sisters (2015 film)|Sisters]]'' (2015).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/02/pitch-perfect-helmer-jason-moore-in-tune-with-tina-fey-for-uni-comedy-the-nest/ |title='Pitch Perfect' Helmer Jason Moore In Tune With Tina Fey For Uni Comedy 'The Nest' |last1=Fleming Jr. |first1=Mike |date=4 February 2013 |publisher=Deadline |accessdate=10 July 2013}}</ref> Pell also played the dream producer and Mom's Anger in the 2015 [[Pixar]] film ''[[Inside Out (2015 film)|Inside Out]]''. In 2016-2018, she starred guest-starred in the TV series ''[[Love (TV Series)|Love]]'' as Erika. She currently plays Helen Henry DeMarcus on the show, ''[[A.P. Bio]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/A.P._Bio|title=A.P. Bio - Wikipedia|website=en.m.wikipedia.org|language=en|access-date=2018-04-14}}</ref> She also plays Aunt Mo in the Showtime series SMILF.
